580
00:55:51,895 --> 00:55:54,731
-I'd like a table.
-Please follow me.

581
00:56:02,864 --> 00:56:05,074
-Can I take your coat?
-Thank you.

582
00:56:06,242 --> 00:56:08,244
Could I get you anything to drink?

583
00:56:09,412 --> 00:56:11,748
-I'd like a beer.
-Certainly.

584
00:56:22,550 --> 00:56:24,761
One, two, one-two-three-four.

585
00:56:26,012 --> 00:56:28,223
That's it for tonight,
ladies and gentlemen.

586
00:56:28,431 --> 00:56:33,144
On the bass, Mr. Larry McVey.
On the drums, Kip Fleming.

587
00:56:33,353 --> 00:56:37,440
And on the guitar,
the one, the only, Mr. Bobby Berman.

588
00:56:37,649 --> 00:56:41,861
We'll be here for the next two weeks,
so please do stop by.

589
00:56:42,111 --> 00:56:44,656
I'm Nick Nightingale. Good night.

590
00:56:55,083 --> 00:56:57,627
-Nick, that was great.
-Thanks.

591
00:56:58,002 --> 00:57:01,339
-Nightingale.
-Hey, Bill, you made it.

592
00:57:01,548 --> 00:57:05,093
I'm sorry, I got here just as you
were finishing your last set.

593
00:57:05,301 --> 00:57:08,346
That's all right.
