642
01:00:22,332 --> 01:00:26,002
Yeah. Look, I'm really sorry
to do this to you, Bill.

643
01:00:27,003 --> 01:00:30,882
I gotta get going. I gotta go.

644
01:00:35,929 --> 01:00:39,891
You know there is no way on earth...

645
01:00:40,350 --> 01:00:43,853
...that you are going to leave here
without taking me with you.

646
01:00:44,521 --> 01:00:48,191
-Come on, buddy, give me a break.
-Nick, I'll tell you what.

647
01:00:48,399 --> 01:00:51,653
I've already got the password.

648
01:00:52,570 --> 01:00:55,740
Just give me the address.
I'll go there by myself...

649
01:00:55,949 --> 01:00:59,536
...and there won't be any connection
between us whatsoever.

650
01:01:02,247 --> 01:01:06,417
Listen, let's just say
for one second...

651
01:01:07,377 --> 01:01:09,587
...that I was prepared to do that.

652
01:01:09,921 --> 01:01:13,258
You couldn't get in anyway
in those clothes.

653
01:01:14,425 --> 01:01:15,760
Why not?

654
01:01:16,219 --> 01:01:20,515
Because everyone is always
costumed and masked.

655
01:01:21,349 --> 01:01:25,019
Where the hell are you gonna
get a costume at this hour?

656
01:01:44,956 --> 01:01:47,125
Thanks. Keep the change.

657
01:02:00,263 --> 01:02:02,557
Yes? Who is it?

658
01:02:02,765 --> 01:02:04,517
Peter, this is Bill Harford.

659
01:02:04,726 --> 01:02:09,147
I apologize for disturbing you
at this hour, but I need your help.

660
01:02:10,273 --> 01:02:12,192
Who is it that you want?

661
01:02:13,776 --> 01:02:16,738
I'm very sorry.
I'm looking for Peter Grenning...

662
01:02:16,988 --> 01:02:19,449
...the owner of Rainbow Fashions.

663
01:02:21,576 --> 01:02:23,077
What's your name?

664
01:02:23,286 --> 01:02:25,622
My name is Bill Harford.

665
01:02:25,830 --> 01:02:28,041
I'm Mr. Grenning's doctor.

666
01:02:29,042 --> 01:02:30,960
You are Grenning's doctor?

667
01:02:34,130 --> 01:02:35,298
Okay.

668
01:02:35,840 --> 01:02:37,300
Just a moment.

669
01:02:52,482 --> 01:02:54,567
You are looking for Peter Grenning?

670
01:02:55,068 --> 01:02:56,361
Yes, I am.

671
01:02:56,861 --> 01:03:00,740
He moved to Chicago over a year ago.

672
01:03:01,533 --> 01:03:03,743
He moved to Chicago?

673
01:03:06,412 --> 01:03:08,456
I wasn't aware of that.

674
01:03:10,416 --> 01:03:14,003
Then are you the present owner
of Rainbow Fashions?

675
01:03:14,212 --> 01:03:15,839
Yes, I am.

676
01:03:16,297 --> 01:03:17,215
Well, first of all...

677
01:03:17,465 --> 01:03:22,345
...please let me apologize again
for disturbing you at this hour, Mr.

678
01:03:22,554 --> 01:03:23,763
Milich.

679
01:03:23,972 --> 01:03:28,143
Mr. Milich. Just to let you know
that I really am Dr. Harford...

680
01:03:28,351 --> 01:03:31,354
...this is my New York State
Medical Board card.

681
01:03:32,272 --> 01:03:35,233
Okay, so you are Dr. Harford.

682
01:03:35,441 --> 01:03:38,862
If I see Peter, I tell him
you were looking for him.

683
01:03:39,070 --> 01:03:41,197
Oh, no, wait. Please, please...

684
01:03:41,823 --> 01:03:45,326
Listen, the reason that
I came here tonight was...

685
01:03:47,370 --> 01:03:52,292
Basically, the reason is
that I need a costume.

686
01:03:52,750 --> 01:03:56,546
And I'd be happy to pay you
$ 1 00 over the rental price...

687
01:03:56,754 --> 01:03:58,423
...for the inconvenience.

688
01:04:00,258 --> 01:04:01,551
A hundred dollars?

689
01:04:05,054 --> 01:04:06,723
I don't think so.

690
01:04:10,185 --> 01:04:12,061
How about $200?

691
01:04:12,687 --> 01:04:15,231
Two hundred dollars
over the rental price?

692
01:04:27,076 --> 01:04:28,328
Come in.

693
01:04:32,790 --> 01:04:35,418
Can't be too careful these days.

694
01:04:38,630 --> 01:04:39,797
Please.

695
01:04:42,550 --> 01:04:45,470
Is it any special costume
you are looking for?

696
01:04:48,515 --> 01:04:53,478
I need a tux, a cloak with a hood
and a mask.

697
01:04:53,937 --> 01:04:56,981
A cloak with a hood and a mask?

698
01:05:00,819 --> 01:05:03,404
I think we'll find something for you.

699
01:05:04,155 --> 01:05:05,824
Follow me, please.

700
01:05:06,366 --> 01:05:07,367
Good.

701
01:05:16,334 --> 01:05:18,503
Looks like alive, huh?

702
01:05:20,255 --> 01:05:22,257
-it's wonderful.
-Come.

703
01:05:23,299 --> 01:05:25,593
So what color cloak?

704
01:05:27,053 --> 01:05:28,763
Red, brown, red?

705
01:05:30,140 --> 01:05:31,224
Black.

706
01:05:31,432 --> 01:05:34,978
The good doctor wouldn't
like something more colorful?

707
01:05:35,186 --> 01:05:37,814
-I don't think so.
-Clowns, officers, pirates?

708
01:05:38,064 --> 01:05:40,692
No, just the tux, the black cloak--

709
01:05:40,900 --> 01:05:43,153
With a hood and a mask.

710
01:05:45,613 --> 01:05:47,115
May I take your coat?

711
01:05:48,992 --> 01:05:52,287
-You are medicine doctor, yes?
-Yes, I am.

712
01:05:53,246 --> 01:05:57,083
-I have some problem with my hair.
-Your hair?

713
01:05:57,292 --> 01:05:59,335
